```
microsoft_graph  ← implemented in SETTINGS.2
smtp             ← future
sendgrid         ← future
mailgun          ← future
aws_ses          ← future
local_dev        ← future
custom           ← future
```

---

## 5. Feature Flag Rules

All ERP email features are gated by `erp_email_feature_flags.is_enabled`.

Seeded flags (all default to `false` except `SYSTEM_TEST_EMAIL`):

```
DMS_EXPIRY_EMAILS
DMS_RENEWAL_EMAILS
HR_EXPIRY_EMAILS
FLEET_EXPIRY_EMAILS
WORKFLOW_EMAILS
REPORT_EMAILS
SYSTEM_TEST_EMAIL  ← true (admin test only)
```

**Do NOT enable email feature flags without Sameer approval.**

---

## 6. DMS Integration Rules

1. **DMS email delivery MUST use ERP Email Settings / Notification Engine** — not hardcoded Graph calls in DMS.
2. **DMS must not store Microsoft credentials** — no tenant_id, client_id, or secrets in DMS tables.
3. **DMS.8 notification queue** (`dms_notification_queue`) remains `email_ready` status until ERP NOTIFICATIONS.1 connects it to the global delivery engine.
4. **DMS.8A** will connect DMS expiry/renewal notifications to the global email delivery engine after ERP NOTIFICATIONS.1.

---

## 7. Permission Codes

```
settings.email.view
settings.email.manage
settings.email.secrets.manage
settings.email.test
settings.email.logs.view
settings.email.feature_flags.manage
```

---

## 8. UI Rules

- Route: `/admin/settings/email`
- Feature folder: `src/features/settings/email/`
- Uses standard ERP settings page layout (not ERPRecordWorkspaceForm)
- Secret input: cleared immediately after save; show only `masked_secret_preview` — never pre-fill
- No client-side secret storage of any kind
- Secret dialog goes through `saveEmailProviderSecret` server action

---

## 9. Send Log Rules

- `erp_email_send_logs.message_preview` stores first 300 chars max — never full body.
- Never log the client secret or access token.
- Log all test connection and test send attempts.

